{
	"mod": [
        "I walk the lonely dao beneath Heaven. Fellow cultivators fade like forgotten scriptures, and my dao-heart devours its own sorrows. Dreams rise and vanish like wandering spirits in the void. I long for a realm where no mortal has stepped, where only the silent sky and endless stars remain. We are hollow cultivators. Our voices whisper without truth of the dao. Form without essence, motion without qi. Those who passed beyond death remember us not as heroes, but as empty vessels wandering the broken path. To live or to perish - such is the question of the dao. Should one endure the tribulations cast by fate, or raise the blade against the sea of suffering? To die is to sleep; yet within that sleep, what dreams may arise after the mortal shell is shed? Our voyage beneath Heaven is finished. The vessel endured every storm of fate, yet the master lies fallen upon the deck. The banners rise and the bells sound, but the one who led us across the endless sea no longer hears their call.",
        "Come, fellow seekers. Though time has weakened our bodies, the will of the dao remains. Let us sail beyond the western stars, toward realms unseen. Though strength fades, the heart of a cultivator endures - to strive, to seek, to find, and never yield. Blind greed and furious wrath drive mortals through their short lives. I saw warriors guarding the abyss, bows drawn and eyes sharp. 'Who descends toward torment?' they cried. 'Speak your purpose - or the arrow will answer. The crimson petals sleep beneath the moon. Fireflies awaken in the silent garden while the stars gaze upon the earth. The world grows still, and the heart opens like a lotus beneath the night sky.",
        "Calamity has descended upon us. You surely remember our ancestral manor, heaven-gazing residence standing arrogantly above the barren moor. This seat spent many years indulging in wine and luxury, yet my Dao Heart eventually grew weary of such mortal decadence. Then rumours reached my ears that beneath the manor lay a gateway to some nameless demonic power, and how could I ignore such a heavenly opportunity? Thus I squandered the clan's remaining spirit stones hiring labourers and arming them with sturdy shovels, excavating beneath the foundations day and night until, within the salt-soaked stone caverns below, we unearthed a cursed portal older than any tribulation, radiating evil qi that shattered the minds of all who beheld it. The earth trembled with every step we took, madness spread like heart demons among the workers, and in the end only this seat fled those blackened halls of antiquity, laughing and wailing until even my consciousness collapsed-thus sealing the ruin of our clan.",
        "Ruin has finally found you. Our heavenly calculations were correct: the balance of Heaven and Earth has been broken. The world now turns upon a strange and terrifying increment, and everywhere the backlash of karma runs wild. This realm has become a wasteland built upon the failures of countless cultivators who came before you, yet you must ride into it without fear. Take this-this final remnant is Hope, the last spark of righteous qi remaining beneath the heavens, and from this moment it belongs to you. You were once a bold cultivator who dared challenge fate itself; now you must be bold once more. Break free from this suffocating stillness, steady your Dao Heart, fix your gaze upon the distant realms, and prepare yourself to face the dreadful truth... of the Keyboard Dao",
        "Do not succumb to despair, disciple. Even in failure there is honour in the attempt, for every step taken upon the Dao tempers the will and refines the spirit. Remain steadfast and undeterred, and you may yet prevail where others have fallen. Reflect upon each trial, study the flaws within your technique and the weakness within your Dao Heart; through repeated tempering your understanding will deepen, and victory will eventually reveal itself. Continue forward-again and again-without retreat. Persist through this murky gloom that clouds your path like demonic mist obscuring the heavens. Walk the road of cultivation endlessly if you must, repeating the cycle of effort and insight, until the veil of ignorance is torn away, the truth of the Dao stands fully revealed before you, and at last you break free from these shackles and achieve enlightenment.",
        "All the tathagatas of the ten directions and the buddhas of the three times appeared through their divine power, suspended within the canopy of the sky. They praised the blessed Tathagata Sakyamuni, saying: 'Good! It is good, Sakyamuni! This king of consecrations is extremely difficult to obtain. The king of vidyas was also consecrated by the former tathagatas established throughout the three times. All of us now declare with a single voice that each of us will likewise consecrate the great king of vidyas, the Light of the Wish-Fulfilling Amogha Jewel. Then each tathagata extended his golden hand and anointed the head of the king of vidyas, bestowing the mudra consecration. The mantra of consecration is: 'Om, amogha jewel-lotus of the great mudra! Blaze! Move forth! Hum!' After granting this consecration, the tathagatas offered their praise and vanished, returning to their own buddha fields."
        ]
}